iOS 26.3 will likely be released to the public later this month, but it appears that Apple is preparing to push out another software update in the interim.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2026/01/iOS-26.2.1-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1031813" /><br/>
Apple's software engineers have started testing iOS 26.2.1, according to the <em>MacRumors</em> visitor logs, which have been a reliable indicator of upcoming iOS versions. The update will likely be released at some point this week or next week.<br/>
<br/>
iOS 26.2.1 should be a minor update with bug fixes and/or security patches.<br/>
<br/>
iOS 26.3 is expected to follow in late January, with <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/12/ios-26-3-new-features/">key new features in that update so far</a> including a new iPhone-to-Android transfer tool, Notification Forwarding for third-party smartwatches in the EU, and more.<div class="linkback">Related Roundups: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-26/">iOS 26</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipados-26/">iPadOS 26</a></div><div class="linkback">Related Forum: <a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/forums/ios-26.248">iOS 26</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/12/ios-26-2-1-coming-soon/">iOS 26.2.1 Update Coming Soon for iPhones</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/ios-26-2-1-update-coming-soon-for-iphones.2475929/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>